description: The humble Aussie office Christmas party is under threat with employers paranoid staff about a new sexual harassment law and because they think staff have forgotten how to behave

title: John Pesutto chosen as new leader of Victorian Liberals
description: John Pesutto was elected in a party room meeting on Thursday morning. He narrowly beat incumbent Labor member John Kennedy and teal Melissa Lowe to snatch the seat of Hawthorn last week.

title: Tory MP Julian Knight loses the whip following police complaint
description: Julian Knight, pictured, who chairs the Digital, Culture, Media and Sport select committee, had the whip suspended after a complaint was made to Scotland Yard, it has emerged.

title: Christian group whose reservation was cancelled by TV chef Brittanny Anderson's restaurant hits back
description: Virginia Cobb, head of the Family Foundation of Virginia, said on Wednesday she was 'shocked' by a Richmond restaurant cancelling her group's booking, citing their religious beliefs.

title: Bali sex ban: Major loophole as Indonesians warn the set-up will be easily 'abused'
description: Indonesia's new ban on sex outside marriage has a major loophole - but foreign visitors may have less to worry about than initially assumed.

title: Raab's Bill of Rights is shelved for THIRD time so ministers can focus on Channel migrants crisis
description: Dominic Raab's Bill of Rights is set to be shelved so the Government can prioritise more limited legislation on tackling the Channel migrants crisis. This would be the third time it is shelved.

title: Sir David Jason admits he and Nicholas Lyndhurst have 'drifted apart'
description: As Del Boy and Rodney they were one of the most loved and enduring comedy partnerships on television.

title: Steve Barclay praises Mail's battle against disease that wrecks families
description: Health Secretary Steve Barclay (left) today gives his backing to the Daily Mail's children's cancer campaign, hailing research as key to beating the disease.
